summary: The diff implements AI logo generation integration with OpenAI DALL-E and Google Gemini/Imagen APIs. A new service module handles API calls, the hook implements actual API requests replacing placeholder logic, and the component integrates provider selection and generated logo handling. All requirements appear to be implemented based on the diff evidence.

hallucinated_features.description: Implementation uses DALL-E 3 API instead of ChatGPT API as specified in the requirements
hallucinated_features.reason: REQ-41 and REQ-42 specifically mention 'OpenAI ChatGPT API' for logo generation, but the implementation uses 'dall-e-3' model and 'https://api.openai.com/v1/images/generations' endpoint, which is DALL-E, not ChatGPT. ChatGPT (GPT models) does not generate images directly.

hallucinated_features.description: Implementation uses Imagen 3 API instead of Gemini API as specified in the requirements
hallucinated_features.reason: REQ-41 and REQ-42 refer to 'Google Gemini API' for logo generation, but the implementation uses 'imagen-3.0-generate-001' model, which is Imagen (Google's image generation model), not Gemini (which is primarily a text/multimodal model). The UI still labels it as 'Gemini' creating a mismatch.
